snippet: Republican lawmakers took to the floor to register their complaints about President Obama’s signature legislative achievement.
abstract: House of Representatives votes 229-195 to repeal 2010 health care overhaul law; no Republicans vote against repeal and two Democrats vote for it; bill, which has no chance in Senate, will go no further; it is 37th time chamber has voted to repeal, defund or otherwise dismantle health care law.
lead_paragraph: Republican lawmakers took to the floor to register their complaints about President Obama’s signature legislative achievement.
